Steps in oxygen emission method

Initial oxygen measurement (O1): The concentration of dissolved oxygen in the ocean is first measured in-situ using oxygen probe (DO meter);
If the device is not available then the sample is collected, fixed and stored for later measurements in the laboratory

Subclasses & orders
Subclass bacillariophycidae

These are raphid (have raphe) pennate diatoms; two orders;

Common genera are;
Genus Corethron (eg. Corethron criophilum – Antarctic diatom with long spines)
Genus Dactyliosolen – forms zig-zag chains (e.g., Dactyliosolen blavyanus)
